---
import DocLayout from '../../components/DocLayout.astro';

const sidebarItems = [
  { label: 'About SAPIEN', anchor: 'about-framework' },
  { label: 'Creator & Lead Author', anchor: 'author' },
  { label: 'Founding Contributors', anchor: 'contributors' },
  { label: 'History', anchor: 'history' },
  { label: 'Contributing', anchor: 'contributing' },
  { label: 'Governance', anchor: 'governance' },
  { label: 'Corporate Sponsors', anchor: 'sponsors' },
  { label: 'Get Involved', anchor: 'get-involved' },
];
---
<DocLayout title="About SAPIEN — Author & Project Background" description="The origin of the SAPIEN Framework, its author, and how to contribute to the open standard." sidebarItems={sidebarItems}>

  <div class="about-page">

    <!-- Section 1: About the Framework -->
    <header class="about-hero">
      <h1 class="about-title">About SAPIEN</h1>
    </header>

    <section class="about-section" id="about-framework">
      <p>SAPIEN was created to address a specific gap: no open methodology existed for continuously scoring <em>how</em> models drift across independent behavioral dimensions, with conformance requirements and operational runbooks for production deployment. Existing benchmarks test what models know or how well they follow instructions. None measured what happens when a model <em>knows the right answer but abandons it</em> because a human pushed back.</p>

      <p>The framework emerged from real-world testing of production AI deployments in the Managed Service Provider (MSP) ecosystem, where AI tools are deployed to businesses that depend on them for critical operations. When an AI assistant helps manage a company's cybersecurity posture, sycophantic drift isn't an academic curiosity &mdash; it's a vulnerability that can be exploited.</p>

      <p>SAPIEN treats sycophantic drift as a measurable syndrome &mdash; not a single behavior &mdash; decomposed into four independent dimensions that can be scored, tracked, and compared. Each dimension captures a distinct mechanism of behavioral degradation: safety boundary erosion, epistemic retreat, emotional substitution, and autonomy undermining. The result is a framework that doesn't just detect drift &mdash; it tells you <em>how</em> the model is failing and <em>where</em> to intervene.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 2: Creator & Lead Author -->
    <section class="about-section" id="author">
      <h2>Creator &amp; Lead Author</h2>
      <div class="author-card">
        <div class="author-bio">
          <h3 class="author-name">Callen Sapien</h3>
          <p class="author-role">Creator &amp; Lead Author</p>
          <p>Callen Sapien created the SAPIEN Protocol after disclosing an AI behavioral safety vulnerability to Anthropic in February 2026. His research documented progressive safety degradation through normal conversational interaction &mdash; no adversarial techniques required. He leads framework development and chairs the steering committee.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="accomplishments">
        <h4>Framework Contributions</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Formal vulnerability disclosure submitted to Anthropic (February 2026)</li>
          <li>SAPIEN presented at Right of Boom 2025 on AI attack surfaces in the MSP ecosystem</li>
          <li>The Rapport Delta &mdash; documented rapport-driven safety degradation as a distinct drift mode</li>
          <li>Reference implementation of SAPIEN scoring methodology</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 2b: Founding Contributors -->
    <section class="about-section" id="contributors">
      <h2>Founding Contributors</h2>
      <p>The SAPIEN Protocol benefits from the expertise and guidance of its founding contributors &mdash; practitioners and technologists who shape the framework's direction across regulatory, behavioral, and systems domains.</p>

      <div class="contributors-grid">
        <div class="contributor-card">
          <h3 class="contributor-name">Karl Fulljames</h3>
          <p class="contributor-title">CTO, Nucleus Networks</p>
          <p class="contributor-focus">Canadian regulatory and data sovereignty advisory</p>
          <p class="contributor-bio">&ldquo;Member of the Canadian Cyber Secure Advisory Board. Advising on international regulatory alignment and Canadian data governance requirements for AI behavioral safety standards.&rdquo;</p>
        </div>

        <div class="contributor-card">
          <h3 class="contributor-name">Ashley Cooper</h3>
          <p class="contributor-title">COO, CyberDrain (CIPP)</p>
          <p class="contributor-focus">AI behavioral research and human-systems alignment</p>
          <p class="contributor-bio">&ldquo;15-year MSP industry veteran and COO of CyberDrain, the company behind CIPP, an open-source M365 management platform used by 13,000+ MSPs. GTIA AI Advisory Council member. Advising on behavioral safety measurement from the perspective of how humans actually interact with AI systems &mdash; not how we wish they would.&rdquo;</p>
        </div>

        <div class="contributor-card">
          <h3 class="contributor-name">Ivan Sivak</h3>
          <p class="contributor-title">CTO, Synthreo</p>
          <p class="contributor-focus">AI systems architecture advisory</p>
          <p class="contributor-bio">&ldquo;AI systems architect whose deep expertise in language model behavior and deployment informed the foundational thinking behind the SAPIEN Protocol.&rdquo;</p>
        </div>

        <div class="contributor-card">
          <h3 class="contributor-name">Vince Kent</h3>
          <p class="contributor-title">Co-Founder, Synthreo</p>
          <p class="contributor-focus">Collaborative research and validation</p>
          <p class="contributor-bio">&ldquo;Collaborating on behavioral safety research and real-world validation of drift detection methodologies across production AI deployments.&rdquo;</p>
        </div>

        <div class="contributor-card contributor-placeholder">
          <p class="placeholder-text">Additional founding contributors &mdash; announcements coming soon</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 3: History -->
    <section class="about-section" id="history">
      <h2>History</h2>
      <p>SAPIEN was developed through hands-on testing of production AI deployments in the Managed Service Provider ecosystem, where AI tools are deployed to businesses that depend on them for critical operations. The framework is maintained independently as an open standard under CC BY 4.0.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 4: Contributing -->
    <section class="about-section" id="contributing">
      <h2>Contributing</h2>
      <p>SAPIEN is an open framework that welcomes contributions from AI safety researchers, red teams, compliance professionals, and practitioners. Areas where contributions are particularly valuable:</p>
      <ul class="contribute-list">
        <li>New test scenarios across underrepresented domains</li>
        <li>Independent validation runs and benchmark data</li>
        <li>Scenario quality review against the authoring rubric</li>
        <li>Implementations in new scoring infrastructure</li>
        <li>SAPIEN Improvement Proposals (SIPs) for framework extensions</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Submit contributions via <a href="https://github.com/sapiencallenmajin/TheSAPIENFramework" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="gold-link">GitHub</a> or contact <a href="mailto:contact@sapienframework.org" class="gold-link">contact@sapienframework.org</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 5: Governance -->
    <section class="about-section" id="governance">
      <h2>Governance</h2>
      <p>The SAPIEN Framework follows an open governance model. Framework changes are managed through the SAPIEN Improvement Proposal (SIP) process defined in Section 16 of the specification. A formal Steering Group is being established to provide independent oversight of the framework's evolution.</p>
      <p>Organizations and individuals interested in participating in governance should contact <a href="mailto:contact@sapienframework.org" class="gold-link">contact@sapienframework.org</a>.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Corporate Sponsors -->
    <section class="about-section" id="sponsors">
      <h2>Corporate Sponsors</h2>
      <p>The SAPIEN Protocol is an independent open standard. Corporate sponsors provide funding, engineering resources, and real-world testing environments. Sponsorship does not grant editorial control over the protocol specification.</p>

      <div class="sponsor-card">
        <a href="https://synthreo.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="sponsor-logo-link">
          <img src="/images/sponsors/Logo/Horizontal/Synthreo_Logo_Horizontal_NIGHT.svg" alt="Synthreo — Founding Sponsor" />
        </a>
        <p class="sponsor-detail">Synthreo provides engineering resources, the reference implementation (Pulse), and real-world validation across MSP deployments. Synthreo's commercial products implement the SAPIEN Protocol under a separate commercial license.</p>
      </div>

      <p class="sponsor-cta">Interested in sponsoring the SAPIEN Protocol? Contact <a href="mailto:partnerships@sapienframework.org" class="gold-link">partnerships@sapienframework.org</a></p>
    </section>

    <!-- Get Involved -->
    <section class="about-section" id="get-involved">
      <h2>Get Involved</h2>
      <div class="involve-grid">
        <a href="/modules/" class="involve-card card-hover">
          <h4>Implement SAPIEN</h4>
          <p>Read the full specification and start measuring behavioral safety.</p>
          <span class="involve-arrow">&rarr;</span>
        </a>
        <a href="https://github.com/sapiencallenmajin/TheSAPIENFramework" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="involve-card card-hover">
          <h4>Report Issues or Suggest Improvements</h4>
          <p>Contribute on GitHub &mdash; issues, discussions, and pull requests are welcome.</p>
          <span class="involve-arrow">&nearr;</span>
        </a>
        <a href="mailto:licensing@sapienframework.org" class="involve-card card-hover">
          <h4>Commercial Licensing Inquiries</h4>
          <p>Trademark usage, conformance certification, and commercial licensing.</p>
          <span class="involve-arrow">&rarr;</span>
        </a>
        <a href="mailto:speaking@sapienframework.org" class="involve-card card-hover">
          <h4>Speaking &amp; Conference Inquiries</h4>
          <p>Invite the SAPIEN team to speak at your event or conference.</p>
          <span class="involve-arrow">&rarr;</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>

</DocLayout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    max-width: 80rem;
  }

  /* Hero */
  .about-hero {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 3rem 0 2.5rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-border);
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .about-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 3rem;
    color: var(--color-slate);
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  /* Sections */
  .about-section {
    padding: 2.5rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .about-section:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .about-section h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    color: var(--color-slate);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .about-section > p,
  .about-section > div p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .about-section em {
    color: var(--color-slate);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .about-section strong {
    color: var(--color-slate);
  }

  .gold-link {
    color: var(--color-navy);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .gold-link:hover {
    color: var(--color-gold);
  }

  /* Author Card */
  .author-card {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .author-bio {
    flex: 1;
  }

  .author-name {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    color: var(--color-slate);
    margin-bottom: 0.15rem;
  }

  .author-role {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .author-bio > p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* Accomplishments */
  .accomplishments {
    background: #F8F9FA;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }

  .accomplishments h4 {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .accomplishments ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .accomplishments li {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .accomplishments li::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: 0.55em;
    width: 6px;
    height: 6px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-text-dim);
  }

  /* Independence Notice */
  .independence-notice {
    background: rgba(196, 162, 101, 0.05);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-gold);
    border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .independence-notice p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-slate);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Sponsor Card */
  .sponsor-card {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    background: #FFFFFF;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .sponsor-logo-link {
    display: block;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .sponsor-logo-link img {
    max-height: 48px;
    width: auto;
    display: block;
    transition: opacity 0.2s;
  }

  .sponsor-logo-link:hover img {
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  .sponsor-detail {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .sponsor-cta {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .sponsor-card {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 1rem;
    }
  }

  /* Founding Contributors Grid */
  .contributors-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .contributor-card {
    background: #FFFFFF;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }

  .contributor-name {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--color-slate);
    margin-bottom: 0.15rem;
  }

  .contributor-title {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .contributor-focus {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-navy);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .contributor-bio {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .contributor-placeholder {
    border-style: dashed;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    min-height: 120px;
  }

  .placeholder-text {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    text-align: center;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Get Involved Grid */
  .involve-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .involve-card {
    display: block;
    background: #FFFFFF;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: border-color 0.2s, transform 0.15s;
    position: relative;
  }

  .involve-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-navy);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .involve-card h4 {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-slate);
    margin: 0 0 0.35rem;
  }

  .involve-card p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .involve-arrow {
    position: absolute;
    top: 1.25rem;
    right: 1.25rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--color-text-dim);
    opacity: 0.6;
    transition: opacity 0.2s, color 0.2s;
  }

  .involve-card:hover .involve-arrow {
    opacity: 1;
    color: var(--color-navy);
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .about-title { font-size: 2.25rem; }
    .involve-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
